    "# Degrading a Spectrum to Lower Resolution\n",
    "\n"
   ]
  },
  {
   "cell_type": "code",
   "execution_count": 3,
   "metadata": {},
   "outputs": [
    {
     "name": "stdout",
     "output_type": "stream",
     "text": [
      "0.1\n"
     ]
    }
   ],
   "source": [
    "import coronagraph as cg\n",
    "print(cg.__version__)"
   ]
  },
  {
   "cell_type": "markdown",
   "metadata": {},
   "source": [
    "### Proxima Centauri Stellar Spectrum\n",
    "\n",
    "First, let's grab the stellar spectral energy distribution (SED) of Proxima Centauri from the VPL website: "
   ]
  },
  {
   "cell_type": "code",
   "execution_count": 4,
   "metadata": {},
   "outputs": [],
   "source": [
    "# The file is located at the following URL:\n",
    "url = \"http://vpl.astro.washington.edu/spectra/stellar/proxima_cen_sed.txt\"\n",
    "\n",
    "# We can open the URL with the following \n",
    "import urllib.request\n",
    "response = urllib.request.urlopen(url)\n",
    "\n",
    "# Read file lines\n",
    "data = response.readlines()\n",
    "\n",
    "# Remove header and extraneous info\n",
    "tmp = np.array([np.array(str(d).split(\"\\\\\")) for d in data[25:]])[:,[1,2]]\n",
    "\n",
    "# Extract columns\n",
    "lam = np.array([float(d[1:]) for d in tmp[:,0]])\n",
    "flux = np.array([float(d[1:]) for d in tmp[:,1]])"
   ]
  },
  {
   "cell_type": "markdown",
   "metadata": {},
   "source": [
    "Now let's set the min and max for our low res wavelength grid, use `construct_lam` to create the low-res wavelength grid, use `downbin_spec` to make a low-res spectrum, and plot it. "
   ]
  },
  {
   "cell_type": "code",
   "execution_count": 5,
   "metadata": {},
   "outputs": [
    {
     "data": {
      "image/png": "\n",
      "text/plain": [
       "<Figure size 1600x1000 with 1 Axes>"
      ]
     },
     "metadata": {
      "image/png": {
       "height": 936,
       "width": 1396
      }
     },
     "output_type": "display_data"
    }
   ],
   "source": [
    "# Set the wavelength and resolution parameters\n",
    "lammin = 0.12\n",
    "lammax = 2.0\n",
    "R = 200\n",
    "dl = 0.01\n",
    "\n",
    "# Construct new low-res wavelength grid\n",
    "wl, dwl = cg.noise_routines.construct_lam(lammin, lammax, dlam = dl)\n",
    "\n",
    "# Down-bin flux to low-res\n",
    "flr = cg.downbin_spec(flux, lam, wl, dlam=dwl)\n",
    "\n",
    "# Plot\n",
    "m = (lam > lammin) & (lam < lammax)\n",
    "plt.plot(lam[m], flux[m])\n",
    "plt.plot(wl, flr)\n",
    "#plt.yscale(\"log\")\n",
    "plt.xlabel(r\"Wavelength [$\\mu$m]\")\n",
    "plt.ylabel(r\"Flux [W/m$^2$/$\\mu$m]\");"
   ]
  },
  {
   "cell_type": "markdown",
   "metadata": {},
   "source": [
    "NaNs can occur when no high-resolution values exist within a given lower-resolution bein. How many NaNs are there?"
   ]
  },
  {
   "cell_type": "code",
   "execution_count": 6,
   "metadata": {},
   "outputs": [
    {
     "name": "stdout",
     "output_type": "stream",
     "text": [
      "0\n"
     ]
    }
   ],
   "source": [
    "print(np.sum(~np.isfinite(flr)))"
   ]
  },
  {
   "cell_type": "markdown",
   "metadata": {},
   "source": [
    "Let's try it again now focusing on the UV with a higher resolution."
   ]
  },
  {
   "cell_type": "code",
   "execution_count": 7,
   "metadata": {},
   "outputs": [
    {
     "data": {
      "image/png": "\n",

       "height": 936,

   "source": [
    "# Set the wavelength and resolution parameters\n",
    "lammin = 0.12\n",
    "lammax = 0.2\n",
    "R = 2000\n",
    "\n",
    "# Construct new low-res wavelength grid\n",
    "wl, dwl = cg.noise_routines.construct_lam(lammin, lammax, R)\n",
    "\n",
    "# Down-bin flux to low-res\n",
    "flr = cg.downbin_spec(flux, lam, wl, dlam=dwl)\n",
    "\n",
    "# Plot\n",
    "m = (lam > lammin) & (lam < lammax)\n",
    "plt.plot(lam[m], flux[m])\n",
    "plt.plot(wl, flr)\n",
    "plt.yscale(\"log\")\n",
    "plt.xlabel(r\"Wavelength [$\\mu$m]\")\n",
    "plt.ylabel(r\"Flux [W/m$^2$/$\\mu$m]\");"
   ]
  },

   "cell_type": "code",
   "execution_count": 8,
   "metadata": {},

    }
   ],
   "source": [
    "print(np.sum(~np.isfinite(flr)))"
   ]
  },
  {
   "cell_type": "markdown",
   "metadata": {},
   "source": [
    "### Optimal Resolution for Observing Earth's O$_2$ A-band  \n",
    "\n",
    "Let's load in the Earth's reflectance spectrum [(Robinson et al., 2011)](http://adsabs.harvard.edu/abs/2011AsBio..11..393R)."
   ]
  },
  {
   "cell_type": "code",
   "execution_count": 9,
   "metadata": {},
   "outputs": [],
   "source": [
    "lamhr, Ahr, fstar = cg.get_earth_reflect_spectrum()"
   ]
  },
  {
   "cell_type": "markdown",
   "metadata": {},
   "source": [
    "Now let's isolate just the O$_2$ A-band."
   ]
  },
  {
   "cell_type": "code",
   "execution_count": 10,
   "metadata": {},
   "outputs": [
    {
     "data": {
      "image/png": "\n",
      "text/plain": [
       "<Figure size 1600x1000 with 1 Axes>"
      ]
     },
     "metadata": {
      "image/png": {
       "height": 1001,
       "width": 1459
      }
     },
     "output_type": "display_data"
    }
   ],
   "source": [
    "lammin = 0.750\n",
    "lammax = 0.775\n",
    "\n",
    "# Create a wavelength mask\n",
    "m = (lamhr > lammin) & (lamhr < lammax)\n",
    "\n",
    "# Plot the band\n",
    "plt.plot(lamhr[m], Ahr[m])\n",
    "plt.xlabel(r\"Wavelength [$\\mu$m]\")\n",
    "plt.ylabel(\"Geometric Albedo\")\n",
    "plt.title(r\"Earth's O$_2$ A-Band\");"
   ]
  },
  {
   "cell_type": "markdown",
   "metadata": {},
   "source": [
    "Define a set of resolving powers for us to loop over."
   ]
  },
  {
   "cell_type": "code",
   "execution_count": 11,
   "metadata": {},
   "outputs": [],
   "source": [
    "R = np.array([1, 10, 30, 70, 100, 150, 200, 500, 1000])"
   ]
  },
  {
   "cell_type": "markdown",
   "metadata": {},
   "source": [
    "Let's down-bin the high-res spectrum at each `R`. For each `R` in the loop we will construct a new wavelength grid, down-bin the high-res spectrum, and plot the degraded spectrum. Let's also save the minimum value in the degraded spectrum to assess how close we get to the actual bottom of the band.  "
   ]
  },
  {
   "cell_type": "code",
   "execution_count": 12,
   "metadata": {},
   "outputs": [
    {
     "data": {
      "image/png": "\n",
      "text/plain": [
       "<Figure size 1600x1000 with 1 Axes>"
      ]
     },
     "metadata": {
      "image/png": {
       "height": 1001,
       "width": 1513
      }
     },
     "output_type": "display_data"
    }
   ],
   "source": [
    "bottom_val = np.zeros(len(R))\n",
    "\n",
    "# Loop over R\n",
    "for i, r in enumerate(R):\n",
    "    \n",
    "    # Construct new low-res wavelength grid\n",
    "    wl, dwl = cg.noise_routines.construct_lam(lammin, lammax, r)\n",
    "\n",
    "    # Down-bin flux to low-res\n",
    "    Alr = cg.downbin_spec(Ahr, lamhr, wl, dlam=dwl)\n",
    "    \n",
    "    # Plot \n",
    "    plt.plot(lamhr[m], Ahr[m], c = \"k\")\n",
    "    plt.plot(wl, Alr, ls = \"steps-mid\", alpha = 0.5, label = \"%i\" %r)\n",
    "    plt.xlim(lammin, lammax)\n",
    "    \n",
    "    # Save bottom value\n",
    "    bottom_val[i] = np.min(Alr)\n",
    "\n",
    "# Finsh plot\n",
    "plt.legend(fontsize = 12, title = r\"$\\lambda / \\Delta \\lambda$\")\n",
    "plt.xlabel(r\"Wavelength [$\\mu$m]\")\n",
    "plt.ylabel(\"Geometric Albedo\")\n",
    "plt.title(r\"Earth's O$_2$ A-Band\");"
   ]
  },
  {
   "cell_type": "markdown",
   "metadata": {},
   "source": [
    "We can now compare the bottom value in low-res spectra to the bottom of the high-res spectrum.  "
   ]
  },
  {
   "cell_type": "code",
   "execution_count": 13,
   "metadata": {},
   "outputs": [
    {
     "data": {
      "image/png": "\n",
      "text/plain": [
       "<Figure size 1600x1000 with 1 Axes>"
      ]
     },
     "metadata": {
      "image/png": {
       "height": 1002,
       "width": 1482
      }
     },
     "output_type": "display_data"
    }
   ],
   "source": [
    "R = np.array(np.linspace(1,1000, 100))\n",
    "bottom_val = np.zeros(len(R))\n",
    "\n",
    "# Loop over R\n",
    "for i, r in enumerate(R): \n",
    "    # Construct new low-res wavelength grid\n",
    "    wl, dwl = cg.noise_routines.construct_lam(lammin, lammax, r)\n",
    "    # Down-bin flux to low-res\n",
    "    Alr = cg.downbin_spec(Ahr, lamhr, wl, dlam=dwl) \n",
    "    # Save bottom value\n",
    "    bottom_val[i] = np.min(Alr)\n",
    "\n",
    "plt.plot(R, bottom_val);\n",
    "plt.xlabel(r\"Resolving Power ($\\lambda / \\Delta \\lambda$)\")\n",
    "plt.ylabel(\"Bottom of the Band Albedo\")\n",
    "plt.title(r\"Earth's O$_2$ A-Band\");"
   ]
  }
 ],
